    "endDate": "2026-04-23T21:00:00+05:30",
    "description": "<p>Marking <em>105 years of legacy</em>, <strong>Vijayalakshmi Silks</strong> presents an immersive exhibition tracing the cultural, social, and retail journey of silk across generations in South India.</p><p>More than a traditional saree showcase, this is a narrative-led experience where textiles are explored as living records of heritage, identity, and memory.</p><p>The exhibition also features a special collaboration with the Mysore Royal Family through the <strong>105 Royal Edit</strong> \u2014 a contemporary collection inspired by royal heirloom sarees. Expect curated presentations by Maharajkumari Kamakshi Devi Wodeyar and Princess Darshika Kumari, bringing together archival richness, royal patronage, and modern interpretation.</p>",
    "image": "https://res.cloudinary.com/puttingscene-com-production/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fputtingscenes-prod-media.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com%2Fevent_images%2F3949%2Fb54fe53c-d43c-43c3-8a98-5e4bda6ead05.jpg",
